{
  "query": "How do the outcomes of using catch protection devices on longlines compare to modifying fishing pots for reducing human-wildlife conflict?",
  "relevant_summary": "Catch protection devices on longlines showed mixed effectiveness in reducing human-wildlife conflict, with successful results in 2 of 4 studies using net sleeves or cage and chain devices to reduce whale damage to fish catches, while other device types showed no significant benefit. Modified fishing pots and traps demonstrated more consistent outcomes, with successful exclusion of sea lions and seals through steel rods or metal frames, and reduced seal damage to salmon catches in multiple studies using wire grids and strengthened netting. Both interventions were effective at reducing unwanted mammal interactions, but modified fishing pots showed more reliable results across multiple studies.",
  "action_ids": [
