  "query": "How does the evidence for modifying fishing pots and traps to exclude mammals compare with installing exclusion or escape devices on fishing nets?",
  "relevant_summary": "The evidence shows that modifying fishing pots and traps to exclude mammals has been studied in six studies, demonstrating effectiveness in reducing marine mammal entrapment (Australian sea lion pups, grey seals, harbour seals) and reducing damage to catches by seals when installing steel rods, metal frames, wire grids, or steel bars with strengthened netting. Installing exclusion devices on fishing nets has been evaluated in seven studies, showing mixed survival outcomes for mammals but successfully reducing trap and entanglement rates for Antarctic fur seals and common bottlenose dolphins in trawl nets.",
