{
  "query": "In the South Pacific and Indian Oceans, what is the best available method for shark control programs to minimize harm to non-target marine mammals?",
  "relevant_summary": "Based on studies in the South Pacific and Indian Oceans, using baited lines instead of nets for shark control is the best available method to minimize harm to non-target marine mammals. Two site comparison studies found that baited lines had fewer entanglements of dolphins, whales, and dugongs compared to nets. One study in the South Pacific Ocean found that using baited lines instead of nets increased the survival of entangled common and bottlenose dolphins. Additionally, using acoustic devices on fishing gear has been shown to reduce marine mammal entanglements in various ocean regions, including the Indian Ocean, though results vary by species and location.",
  "action_ids": [
